JOHANNESBURG - The bail application of Sandile Mantsoe, the man accused of killing Karabo Mokoena, has been postponed until 9 June in the Johannesburg Magistrate's Court.The magistrate earlier barred media from broadcasting proceedings.Mantsoe is charged with premeditated murder and defeating the ends of justice.The killing of Mokoena sparked a vital debate about domestic violence in South Africa.Her burnt body was found in a veld in Lyndhurst, eastern Johannesburg, last month.*Specialist reporter Karyn Maughan was in court and comments on the case in the video aboveeNCA